      "description": "<p>We are a small / medium sized company in Hamburg. Take-off was 2015 with the aerospace industry. Our base is in the ZAL-TechCenter close to our airborn customers Airbus, Premium Aerotec, Lufthansa Technik etc. Since then we were also heading towards the automotive and maritime and medical industry. Our products and solutions include b2b software for advanced AI computer vision and IoT based assistance systems to enable our customers with the latest digital technologies.</p>\n<p><strong>Tasks</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Implement apis with (e.G. GraphQL or gRPC web) for our microservice architecture</li>\n<li>Write microservices with gRPC communication that control robots</li>\n<li>Create connectors to industrial devices (e.G. via TCP protocols)</li>\n<li>Connect and query graph databases like dGraph or Neo4j</li>\n<li>Define software architectures with our young and dynamic team</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>You just need to love Go.</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work in a company where people love what they do</li>\n<li>Create awesome stuff, learn as you go</li>\n<li>Work from home or come to our office with river view</li>\n<li>Equipment is high end, choose your os, editor</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Come as you are.</p>\n",
