      "company": "Synetec Ltd",
      "company_url": "https://synetec.co.uk/",
      "location": "London",
      "title": "Mid Level .Net Developer",
      "description": "<p>Synetec are looking for an enthusiastic, conscientious and technically skilled Mid Level .Net developer to work within the Development Team and who will report to the Head of Delivery.</p>\n<p>The role will be to assist in the design and then develop the solutions that are needed to support the growing business and trading platforms. The individual will be influential in the analysis, design, development, and ongoing maintenance of these class leading platforms, whilst liaising with a Product Owner and fellow developers. The person will be working within a small IT team, reporting to the Head of Delivery and will be comfortable in a fast-paced, entrepreneurial, team-orientated environment and will be required to:</p>\n<p>Participate in an Agile project team with an emphasis on delivery and client value\nBe included in scrum team responsibilities, e.g. review presentation, etc.\nProvide code reviews and “buddy testing”\nHelp mentor and support Junior Developers\nCommit to self-improvement, learning and progression\nAttend appropriate meet-ups for client projects and internal team development\nResearch new technologies as they become relevant\nEssential Skills:</p>\n<p>Minimum of 4 years C# commercial experience\nGood knowledge/experience of design patterns(repository &amp; UoW)\nStrong C# .Net developer, with proven experience working on server-side multi-threaded systems.\nGood knowledge of .Net development\nGood knowledge of Domain Driven Design\nGood Entity Framework skills.\nGood Microservices experience\nGood knowledge/experience of writing testable software\nComfortable joining an Agile Scrum team\nExcellent written and spoken English\nGood knowledge/experience with GIT software repository</p>\n<p>What we can offer you:</p>\n<p>Salary: £55,000 to £65,000, depending on experience.\nFlexible working hours, home and office\nUp-skilling/training opportunities\nPrivate healthcare after qualifying period\nGenerous leave allowance of 23 days as well as all working days off between Christmas and New Year’s Day\nCulture of inclusivity\nGreat location in London near London Bridge, Southwark and Waterloo stations. Remote working during COVID restrictions.\nImmediate start available</p>\n",
      "how_to_apply": "<p>Email your CV to <a href=\"mailto:careers@synetec.co.uk\">careers@synetec.co.uk</a></p>\n",
